## Secrets in AWS Secrets Manager (us-east-1)

| Secret | Endpoint | Status |
|--------|----------|--------|
| `/bsd/prod/go/tx/us2` | New NLB (working) | Active ŌĆö refreshed by this app |
| `/bsd/prod/go/tx/eu2` | New NLB | Token updated but no pod reads it |
| `/bsd/prod/go/tx/us` | Old dead ELB | Broken ŌĆö ELB decommissioned |
| `/bsd/prod/go/tx/eu` | Old dead ELB | Broken ŌĆö ELB decommissioned |

## Permanent Fix Needed

The current approach is a band-aid. The proper fix requires:
1. Wire up `PlaylistApi` in `bsd-go-mediator-tokens/src/app/service.ts` to actually connect, get tokens, and write them to Secrets Manager periodically
2. Update `bsd-go-tx-sync` to periodically re-read the token from Secrets Manager instead of caching once at startup
